3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Delhi%20high%20court%20on%20Monday%20(October%209)%20reserved%20its%20judgment%20in%20the%20pleas%20filed%20by%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20founding%20editor%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20and%20HR%20head%20Amit%20Chakraborty%20challenging%20the%20remand%20order%20issued%20after%20their%20arrest.%20The%20two%20were%20arrested%20on%20October%203%20in%20relation%20to%20an%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPurkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%20have%20also%20challenged%20the%20FIR%20against%20them%2C%20and%20the%20judge%20will%20decide%20if%20notice%20is%20to%20be%20sent%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20on%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Tushar%20Rao%20Gedela%20reserved%20the%20judgment%20after%20hearing%20both%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20counsel%20and%20the%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20lawyer.%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20appeared%20for%20the%20Delhi%20Police.%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArguing%20for%20Purkayastha%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Kapil%20Sibal%20said%20that%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20were%20not%20provided%20at%20the%20time%20of%20arrest%20or%20even%20in%20the%20remand%20order%2C%20thus%20going%20against%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20on%20arrests.%20The%20editor%20was%20also%20not%20allowed%20to%20have%20a%20lawyer%20of%20his%20choice%20present%20during%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20remand%20order%2C%20it%20was%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESibal%20also%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20a%20rupee%2C%20not%20a%20penny%E2%80%9D%20had%20come%20from%20China%20to%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Purkayastha.%20The%20Delhi%20Police%20FIR%20%E2%80%93%20which%20casts%20a%20wide%20net%2C%20ranging%20from%20Chinese%20phone%20producers%20to%20lawyers%20to%20protesting%20farmers%20%E2%80%93%20has%20claimed%20that%20the%20portal%20received%20Chinese%20government%20funding%20to%20spread%20propaganda.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20Sibal%20and%20senior%20advocate%20Dayan%20Krishnan%2C%20appearing%20for%20Purkayastha%2C%20referred%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20last%20week%20judgment%20in%20the%20case%20of%20%3Cem%3EPankaj%20Bansal%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20which%20the%20court%20had%20said%20that%20a%20written%20copy%20of%20the%20grounds%20for%20arrest%20must%20be%20provided%20to%20an%20accused%20at%20the%20time%20of%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20magistrate%20who%20sent%20Purkayastha%20and%20Chakraborty%20to%20seven%20days%20police%20remand%20did%20not%20ensure%20that%20this%20had%20been%20followed%2C%20and%20also%20did%20not%20check%20if%20the%20accused%20had%20access%20to%20their%20lawyers%2C%20Krishnan%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehta%20said%20that%20petitioners%20had%20been%20told%20about%20the%20grounds%20for%20arrest.%20He%20argued%20that%20under%20UAPA%20guidelines%2C%20a%20written%20copy%20is%20not%20essential.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696839003000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F09132731%2Fnewsclick.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-hc-reserves-judgment-on-pleas-challenging-remand-orders-of-newsclick-editor-hr-head%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lawyers%20appearing%20for%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20and%20Amit%20Chakraborty%20argued%20that%20the%20two%20had%20not%20been%20informed%20about%20the%20grounds%20for%20arrest%20on%20time.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-hc-reserves-judgment-on-pleas-challenging-remand-orders-of-newsclick-editor-hr-head%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chinese%20Woman%20Sues%20Daughter%2C%20Son-In-Law%20For%20Raising%20Their%20Son%20For%205%20Years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20Chinese%20woman%20has%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20her%20daughter%20and%20son-in-law%20and%20is%20demanding%20%2426%2C000%20compensation%20for%20taking%20care%20of%20her%20grandson%20for%20five%20years%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fpeople-culture%2Fsocial-welfare%2Farticle%2F3236107%2Fchinese-woman-sues-daughter-and-son-law-us26000-raising-their-son-5-years-she-feels-efforts-not%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESouth%20China%20Morning%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20The%20woman%2C%20known%20by%20her%20surname%20Duan%20from%20Guangan%20City%20in%20Sichuan%20province%2C%20located%20in%20southwestern%20China%20provided%20care%20for%20her%20grandson%20from%20February%202018%20to%20July%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20outlet%20reported%20that%20Duan's%20daughter%2C%20surnamed%20Hu%2C%20and%20her%20son-in-law%2C%20surnamed%20Zhu%20did%20not%20have%20time%20for%20their%20child%2C%20whose%20age%20is%20not%20disclosed.%20The%20couple%20were%20employed%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Chengdu%20and%20they%20sent%20Duan%20a%20monthly%20stipend%20of%201%2C000%20yuan%20(US%24135)%20and%20a%20childcare%20fee%20of%202%2C000%20yuan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20five%20years%20of%20providing%20childcare%20without%20complaint%2C%20she%20decided%20that%20she%20deserved%20further%20compensation.%20She%20asked%20the%20couple%20to%20pay%20her%20%2426%2C000.%20Hu%20promised%20to%20pay%2050%2C000%20yuan%20(US%246%2C800)%20to%20her%20mother%20and%20they%20signed%20an%20agreement%2C%20the%20media%20outlet%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Hu%20did%20not%20complete%20the%20payment%20despite%20frequent%20reminders%20by%20her%20mother.%20Then%20Duan%20sued%20the%20couple.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20that%20she%20did%20not%20have%20a%20legal%20obligation%20to%20take%20care%20of%20her%20grandson%20but%20acknowledged%20her%20entitlement%20to%20a%20childcare%20fee%20from%20the%20couple.%20However%2C%20the%20court%20also%20found%20the%20amount%20she%20demanded%20was%20excessive%20and%20decided%20to%20revise%20it%20to%2082%2C500%20yuan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EZhu%20in