%3EIn%201978%2C%20a%20yet%20unknown%20sub-population%20of%20just%2014%20Siberian%20Cranes%20were%20discovered%20by%20Dr.%20Ali%20Ashtiani%20wintering%20at%20Fereydunkenar%20wetland%20in%20Iran%20where%20local%20people%20trapped%20wild%20ducks%20and%20geese.%20This%20was%20nothing%20short%20of%20a%20miracle.%20In%201985%2C%20Dr.%20Yuri%20Markin%20attached%20a%20satellite%20transmitter%20to%20a%20male%20crane%20in%20Iran%20to%20discover%20a%20new%20breeding%20ground%20of%20this%20bird%20in%20Siberia.%20The%20Iranian%20sub-population%20unfortunately%20followed%20the%20same%20trajectory%20as%20the%20Indian%20one.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%202002%20only%20four%20birds%20remained%2C%20the%20population%20continued%20to%20dwindle%20and%20soon%20only%20one%20pair%2C%20the%20male%20named%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(%E2%80%9Chope%E2%80%9D%20in%20Persian)%20and%20female%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EArezoo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(%E2%80%9Cwish%E2%80%9D%20in%20Persian)%20remained.%20In%202006%20or%202007%20only%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20returned%2C%20he%20had%20lost%20his%20mate%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EArezoo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EReintroduction%20programmes%20in%20Russia%20failed%20to%20revive%20the%20population.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20living%20up%20to%20his%20name%2C%20has%20since%20appeared%20each%20autumn%2C%20spending%20four%20winter%20months%20in%20Iran%20consecutively%20for%20the%20past%2015%20years%2C%20making%20him%20the%20only%20known%20survivor%20of%20the%20western%20population%20of%20Siberian%20cranes%20in%20the%20wild%20who%20retains%20the%20ancient%20knowledge%20of%20the%20migration%20route.%20No%20one%20knows%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20exact%20age%2C%20in%20captivity%2C%20their%20lifespan%20has%20been%20recorded%20up%20to%20about%2070%20years%2C%20lifespans%20in%20the%20wild%20are%20shorter.%20The%20continued%20presence%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20a%20certain%20area%20every%20winter%20has%20made%20it%20possible%20to%20protect%20and%20help%20him%20at%20least%20when%20he%20is%20in%20Iran.%20His%20migration%20path%20is%20over%205%2C000%20kms%20and%20there%20are%20many%20dangers%20on%20this%20route.%20His%20survival%20so%20far%20is%20a%20miracle%20and%20a%20cause%20for%20hope.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20female%2C%20it%20was%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20before%20this%20population%20would%20be%20extinguished%20forever.%20I%20had%20thus%20ended%20my%20article%20on%20a%20note%20of%20foreboding.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20I%20recently%20came%20across%20an%20astonishing%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.presstv.ir%2FDetail%2F2023%2F03%2F06%2F699370%2FOmid-Last-Siberian-Crane-Leaves-Iran-Winters-Rouya%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eupdate%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20this%20winter%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20had%20flown%20back%20not%20alone%2C%20but%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20female%20Siberian%20Crane!%20The%20Cracid%20%26amp%3B%20Crane%20Breeding%20and%20Conservation%20Center%2C%20(CBCC)%20in%20Belgium%20had%20brought%20up%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20meaning%20%E2%80%98dream%E2%80%99%20in%C2%A0Persian%20%E2%80%93%20in%20captivity%20at%20their%20facility%20and%20with%20the%20Iranian%20government%20and%20other%20stakeholders%2C%20had%20released%20her%20in%20stages%20with%20Omid.%20And%20after%20they%20spent%20part%20of%20the%20winter%20together%2C%20they%20flew%20back%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThrough%20a%20network%20of%20phone%20calls%20and%20Facebook%20messages%20%E2%80%93%20thanks%20to%20conservationist%20Gopi%20Sundar%20and%20Taej%20Mundkur%20%E2%80%93%20I%20was%20able%20to%20contact%20Keramat%20Hafezi%20Birgani%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Khuzestan%20Biodiversity%20Group.%20I%20emailed%20him%20to%20immediately%20receive%20a%20response%20accompanied%20by%20his%20detailed%20report%20%E2%80%98Hope%20and%20effort%20for%20the%20dream%20of%20life%20and%20survival%E2%80%99%20that%20appeared%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20Crane%20Conservation%20Group%20Newsletter%2C%202023%20Volume%201.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20312px)%2085vw%2C%20312px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193503%2F02-Roya-Keramat-1-300x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22312%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193503%2F02-Roya-Keramat-1-300x300.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193503%2F02-Roya-Keramat-1-150x150.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193503%2F02-Roya-Keramat-1.jpg%20781w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678965%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22312%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERoya%2C%20the%20captive%20bred%20female%20released%20alongside%20Omid%20with%20the%20blue%20ring%20on%20one%20of%20its%20leg.%20Photo%3A%20Keramat%20Hafezi%20Birgani%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202022%2C%20George%20Archibald%20of%20the%20International%20Crane%20Foundation%20(ICF)%20had%20informed%20Keramat%20that%20there%20was%20a%20suitable%20Siberian%20Crane%20female%20at%20the%20CBCC.%20Keramat%20helped%20connect%20the%20CBCC%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Environment%20(DoE)%2C%20Iran%20and%20the%20ICF%20was%20requested%20to%20help%20Iran.%20The%20CBCC%2C%20with%20many%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20breeding%20Siberian%20cranes%20and%20other%20endangered%20species%2C%20opened%20and%20maintained%20valuable%20communication%20and%20cooperation%20with%20the%20DoE.%20The%20planned%20release%20of%20Roya%20was%20potentially%20the%20most%20crucial%20initiative%20to%20save%20the%20Iranian%20sub-population%20and%20a%20big%20step%20for%20the%20survival%20of%20the%20species.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EQuite%20aptly%20named%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Roya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20seven-year-old%20female%20Crane%20was%20in%20perfect%20health.%20On%20arrival%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20placed%20in%20a%20special%20release%20cage%20near%20Omid%E2%80%99s%20habitat.%20The%20birds%20started%20interacting%20almost%20immediately.%20After%20closely%20monitoring%20the%20two%20together%2C%20their%20interaction%2C%20calls%20and%20behaviour%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20released%20on%20January%2031%2C%202023.%20In%20a%20dream-like%20sequence%2C%20almost%20immediately%20on%20release%2C%20both%20cranes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.mehrnews.com%2Fnews%2F197148%2FVIDEO-Siberian-cranes-Roya-Omid-in-Iran-for-cold-season%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecalled%20beautifully%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20danced%20together%2C%20soon%20the%20birds%20started%20to%20fly%2C%20explore%20the%20wetlands%20and%20feed%20together.%20In%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20release%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20came%20from%20north%20of%20the%20wetland%20to%20see%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20stayed%20a%20few%20hours%2C%20the%20time%20spent%20together%20increased%20every%20day%2C%20and%20soon%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20flew%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20roost%20in%20the%20northern%20areas%20of%20the%20wetland.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESiberian%20cranes%20of%20the%20CBCC%20are%20descendants%20of%20the%20cranes%20of%20the%20western%20population%20of%20Russia.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20though%20captive-bred%2C%20was%20raised%20with%20virtually%20no%20contact%20with%20humans%2C%20this%20was%20crucial%20for%20her%20re-wilding.%20Her%20vigilance%20and%20natural%20instinct%20were%20excellent%2C%20after%20soft%20release%2C%20she%20was%20alert%20and%20fresh%2C%20she%20fed%20on%20food%20from%20the%20appropriate%20environment%2C%20and%20also%20adapted%20against%20the%20dangers%20of%20wild%20such%20as%20the%20night%2C%20the%20fog%2C%20predators%20like%20the%20Golden%20Jackal%2C%20Jungle%20Cat%2C%20Eurasian%20Otter%2C%20as%20well%20as%20birds%20of%20prey%20such%20as%20the%20White-tailed%20Sea%20Eagle%2C%20Greater%20Spotted%20Eagle%2C%20Eastern%20Imperial%20Eagle%2C%20Northern%20Goshawk%2C%20and%20Black%20Kite.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20bravely%20adapted%20to%20the%20wilderness%20and%20benefited%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20company.%20As%20the%20end%20of%20the%20winter%20migration%20came%20closer%2C%20they%20flew%20together%20around%20the%20wetland%2C%20they%20danced%20and%20called.%20The%20morning%20of%20March%205%2C%202023%2C%20was%20sunny%20and%20calm%2C%20everybody%20involved%20watched%20with%20bated%20breath.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20had%20arrived%20in%20Iran%20on%20October%2027%2C%20after%20130%20days%20of%20wintering%20which%20included%2034%20days%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%2C%20Omid%20and%20Roya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20took%20off%20together%20and%20started%20their%20spring%20migration%2C%20passing%20the%20Sorkh%20Rood%20Lagoon%20on%20their%20long%20and%20perilous%20flight%20from%20Fereydunkenar%20wetland%20to%20Western%20Siberia.%20The%20toughest%20section%20of%20this%20marvellous%20journey%20had%20just%20begun%2C%20anything%20could%20happen.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193555%2F03-Roya-Omid-Keramat.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22781%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193555%2F03-Roya-Omid-Keramat.jpg%20781w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193555%2F03-Roya-Omid-Keramat-300x300.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193555%2F03-Roya-Omid-Keramat-150x150.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678966%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22781%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOmid%20and%20Roya%20soon%20after%20Roya%E2%80%99s%20release.%20Photo%3A%20Keramat%20Hafezi%20Birgani%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20euphoric%20start%2C%20the%20team%20confronted%20their%20first%20real%20roadblock.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20seen%20alone%20on%20the%20migration%20route%2C%20fortunately%20she%20was%20healthy.%20On%20March%2012%2C%202023%20she%20was%20successfully%20captured%20for%20safe%20keeping.%20While%20there%20was%20disappointment%2C%20it%20was%20also%20true%20that%20all%20was%20not%20lost.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20would%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20be%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20again%20in%20the%20autumn%20of%202023%20with%20the%20hope%20that%20they%20will%20be%20successful%20the%20second%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%20summers%20in%20a%20vast%20area%20and%20finding%20him%20is%20like%20finding%20a%20needle%20in%20a%20haystack.%20All%20the%20same%2C%20Russian%20collaborators%20had%20expressed%20their%20readiness%20to%20release%20young%20Siberian%20cranes%20from%20their%20Oka%20Crane%20Breeding%20Center%20into%20Omid%E2%80%99s%20summering%20area%2C%20with%20the%20idea%20that%20they%20might%20join%20him%20on%20his%20journey%20to%20Iran.%20The%20CBCC%20had%20also%20announced%20its%20readiness%20to%20donate%20Siberian%20cranes%20that%20will%20be%20born%20this%20summer%20to%20Iran%20to%20be%20released%20in%20autumn%202023%20to%20potentially%20accompany%20Omid%20and%20Roya%20on%20their%20journey%20back.%20All%20these%20measures%20depend%2C%20of%20course%2C%20on%20the%20safe%20return%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOmid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20if%20all%20goes%20as%20normal%20is%20just%20a%20few%20weeks%20away.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20brief%20history%20of%20release%20attempts%20that%20did%20not%20succeed%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERoya%E2%80%99s%20release%20was%20not%20the%20first%20attempt%20to%20revive%20the%20crane%20population.%20According%20to%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cms.int%2Fsiberian-crane%2Fen%2Fpage%2Freintroduction%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20from%201991%20to%202010%2C%20a%20total%20of%20139%20Siberian%20Cranes%20that%20originated%20from%20captive-produced%20eggs%20have%20been%20released%20at%20the%20breeding%20and%20wintering%20grounds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20there%20were%20unconfirmed%20reports%20of%20banded%20cranes%20along%20the%20migration%20route%20several%20hundred%20kms%20from%20their%20release%20area%2C%20none%20of%20these%20cranes%20were%20observed%20on%20the%20known%20wintering%20or%20summer%20grounds.%20The%20vast%20inaccessible%20nature%20of%20the%20Siberian%20wilderness%2C%20low%20human%20numbers%20and%20high%20costs%20to%20survey%20and%20satellite-track%20only%20add%20to%20the%20difficulty.%20This%20has%20also%20made%20it%20difficult%20to%20evaluate%20the%20success%20of%20the%20release%20experiments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20254px)%2085vw%2C%20254px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193226%2F07-Stamp_of_India_-_1983_-_Colnect_168539_-_Siberian_Crane_Grus_leucogeranus-226x300.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22254%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193226%2F07-Stamp_of_India_-_1983_-_Colnect_168539_-_Siberian_Crane_Grus_leucogeranus-226x300.jpeg%20226w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193226%2F07-Stamp_of_India_-_1983_-_Colnect_168539_-_Siberian_Crane_Grus_leucogeranus.jpeg%20253w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678961%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22337%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20stamp%20issued%20in%201983%2C%20when%20hopes%20of%20saving%20the%20Indian%20sub-population%20of%20the%20Siberian%20Cranes%20were%20still%20high.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20these%20139%2C%20over%20several%20years%2C%2010%20juvenile%20captive-reared%20cranes%20were%20released%20in%20late%20winter%20near%20the%20wild%20ones%20at%20Keoladeo%20National%20Park%20(KNP)%20in%20India.%20While%20their%20feeding%20behaviour%20and%20daily%20activities%20were%20similar%20to%20the%20wild%20cranes%2C%20they%20did%20not%20socialise%20extensively%20with%20them%20and%20did%20not%20migrate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPerhaps%20the%20late%20winter%20releases%20did%20not%20allow%20enough%20time%20for%20the%20released%20birds%20to%20develop%20enough%20social%20bonds%20with%20the%20wild%20ones%20for%20them%20to%20fly%20together%20and%20disappeared%20due%20to%20a%20variety%20of%20factors.%20The%20experiment%2C%20however%2C%20confirmed%20that%20captive-reared%20cranes%20could%20survive%20in%20the%20wild%20throughout%20the%20year%20at%20KNP%2C%20but%20it%20unlikely%20that%20they%20could%20breed%20at%20such%20southern%20latitudes.%20The%20last%20wild%20pair%20of%20Siberian%20Cranes%20wintering%20in%20India%20did%20not%20return%20in%202003%20and%20the%20attempts%20at%20KNP%20came%20to%20an%20end.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20story%20in%20Iran%20is%20not%20very%20different.%20Two%20adult%20captive%20parent-reared%20males%20were%20released%20in%20winter%20of%201996-97%20in%20Fereydunkenar.%20Quite%20like%20in%20India%2C%20they%20did%20not%20join%20the%20wild%20cranes%20and%20did%20not%20migrate.%20One%20of%20them%20was%20recaptured%20and%20held%20in%20captivity%20but%20it%20died%20in%202006.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERelease%20was%20resumed%20in%20winter%202002-03.%20A%20total%20of%2011%20captive-reared%20cranes%20were%20released%20at%20Fereydunkenar.%20All%20were%20ringed%20with%20colour%20plastic%20bands%2C%20three%20were%20also%20fitted%20with%20satellite%20transmitters%20which%20stopped%20working%20after%20a%20short%20time%20or%20just%20after%20migration%20started.%20Three%20of%20them%20died%20and%20eight%20started%20migration%20along%20with%20wild%20cranes.%20One%20crane%20released%20in%20Iran%20in%20winter%20of%202007-08%20was%20sighted%20in%20spring%202008%20at%20breeding%20grounds%20in%20Khanty-Mansiysk%20Autonomous%20Region%20of%20west%20Siberia%2C%20however%20none%20of%20the%20cranes%20returned%20to%20the%20wintering%20grounds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPeeyush%20Sekhsaria%2C%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20architect-geographer%20and%C2%A0independent%20development%20consultant.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696774310000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F08193903%2FScreenshot-2021-07-23-at-10.43.00-AM-2048x1236-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthere-is-still-some-omid-siberian-crane-revival%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Omid%2C%20the%20only%20known%20survivor%20of%20the%20western%20population%20of%20Siberian%20cranes%20in%20the%20wild%2C%20has%20wintered%20in%20Iran%20consecutively%20for%20the%20past%2015%20years%2C%20alone.%20But%20not%2